==English==

===Etymology===
French phrase "Fool the eye," ''tromper:'' to fool, to deceive, to trick and ''l'œil:'' the eye

===Noun===
'''trompe-l'œil''' ''or'' '''trompe l'oeil'''

# ultra-realistic painting technique which attempts to make a 2-dimensional image appear to be a real 3-dimensional object

